The family members allegedly caught trying to sneak into Syria with the son of a Labour councillor have been arrested after being brought back to the UK from Turkey .
Two women aged 47 and 22 , and two men aged 24 and 22 were held at Manchester Airport in the early hours of this morning .
They were among eight relatives stopped at the Turkish border with Syria on April 1 with university student Waheed Ahmed , the 21-year-old son of Labour councillor Shakil Ahmed .
